{"title":"In the desert","author":{"name":"Stephen Crane"},"publishDate":"2011-05-10","lines":[{"line":"In the desert","stanza":1,"number":1},{"line":"I saw a creature, naked, bestial,","stanza":1,"number":2},{"line":"Who, squatting upon the ground,","stanza":1,"number":3},{"line":"Held his heart in his hands,","stanza":1,"number":4},{"line":"And ate of it.","stanza":1,"number":5},{"line":"I said: “Is it good, friend?”","stanza":1,"number":6},{"line":"“It is bitter – bitter,” he answered;","stanza":1,"number":7},{"line":"“But I like it","stanza":1,"number":8},{"line":"Because it is bitter,","stanza":1,"number":9},{"line":"And because it is my heart.”","stanza":1,"number":10}]}